title: Fatal accident on W. KY Parkway closes lanes
text:
Police are investigating the scene of a fatal accident on Western Kentucky Parkway this Sunday.
WHAS 11 reported earlier the accident occurred near mile marker 123, close to the Sonora/Harding Springs exit 15 miles west of Elizabethtown. Kentucky State Troopers confirmed that the accident was fatal around 10 a.m.
The highway is expected to reopen in about an hour, according to a WLKY story .
There is little information regarding what caused the accident but it is confirmed to have involved two vehicles.
